import numpy as np
def stats_average_and_std(numbers):
    if not all(isinstance(x, (int, float)) for x in numbers):
        raise ValueError("All elements must be numeric.")
    
    average = sum(numbers) / len(numbers)
    std_deviation = np.std(numbers)
    
    return average, std_deviation
# Example usage:
nums = [10, 23, 45, 67, 89]
average, standard_deviation = stats_average_and_std(nums)
